The paper presents a new model, the Neural Transducer, which is designed to make incremental predictions as more input arrives. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category (cs.CL) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions that the model can be trained using dynamic programming, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions that the model performs well on long sequences, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
